Liverpool team pose before the UEFA Champions league semi-final second leg football match between Liverpool and Barcelona at Anfield in Liverpool, north west England on May 7, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - Premier League leaders Liverpool have reversed their decision to place some non-playing staff on temporary leave. Club CEO Peter Moore has also apologised to fans after the decision drew sharp criticism from the British government and supporters. READ: Bayern Munich to resume training They were also holding talks about salary deductions for players and senior staff. The Premier League was suspended last month over the coronavirus outbreak.